China Media Group (CMG), the country's major broadcaster, is joining hands with media partners worldwide to deliver the real-time pulse of the Olympic Winter Games Beijing 2022 to global spectators with cutting-edge technologies. CMG, a rights-holding broadcaster of the Winter Games, hosted a forum on Wednesday in Beijing under the theme of "Together for a High-tech Winter Olympics." Representatives of 145 media agencies and international organizations from 78 countries and regions attended the event online.